<p><abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ draft ]">Dft</abbr> does not delete give; TJ first wrote the phrase as given in brackets, then added t to no, deleted disquietude to and interlined disquiet. The presence of in interlined and deleted <span class="pb" title="page number in print edition" id="TSJN-01-01-02-pb-0199">[199<a style="padding-left: 0px" onclick="window.open('/img-document-get.xqy?image=TSJN/Pages/TSJN-01-01/TSJN-01-01-02-pb-0199.jpg', 'pageImage', 'scrollbars=1,resizable=1'); return false" onkeypress="this.onclick();" tabindex="0" title="Click to view image of page from print edition"><img src="/img-ML/page-icon.gif" width="18" height="20" style="vertical-align:middle;" alt="page icon"/></a>]</span> above the first syllable of disquietude suggests that TJ may first have altered the phrase to make it read may give no inquietude to but that, in further changing it, he neglected to strike out give.</p></div>
